Actis, Mon Loisir to Invest $180 Million in Mauritius: L’Express

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-04-18T05:50:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/actis-mon-loisir-to-invest-180-million-in-mauritius-l-express.html
Groupe Mon Loisir and Actis LLP
plan to build a village on the east coast of Mauritius at a cost
of 5 billion rupees ($180 million), Port Louis’s l’Express
newspaper said, citing Murray Adair, chief executive officer of
Indian Ocean Real Estate Company Ltd., which is equally owned by
the two companies.  To contact the reporter on this story: Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port
Louis via Johannesburg at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  